<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-12T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-12T10:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">745.93/10–1249: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Holmes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-12T16:00:00+01:00">October
                                    12, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 12—12:22 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4092. Indian High Commissioner informed American correspondent in
                            confidence October 10 Nehru had (1) recalled Indian Ambassador China,
                            (2) exchanged cordial messages with Mme. Sun Yatsen<note n="19" xml:id="d136fn19">Member of Communist-sponsored Chinese People’s
                                Political Consultative Conference and a Vice Chairman of the
                                “Central Government of the People’s Republic of China”.</note> and
                            (3) sent favorable and friendly reply Communist Foreign Minister re
                            establishment Central People’s Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Holmes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>